<HEADLINE>
FT  29 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Caverdale buy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Caverdale, the motor retailing and industrial products group, has acquired
GE Harper, a Volkswagen and Audi dealer, for Pounds 2.4m in cash.
The acquisition will be financed from existing resources and from the sale
of a stake worth Pounds 1.56m in United Dutch Group.
Harper made pre-tax profits of Pounds 130,000 in 1993 on turnover of Pounds
4.8m. Caverdale now holds 16 vehicle franchises in 25 locations.
