<HEADLINE>
FT  29 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Philip Harris jumps to Pounds 0.95m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Philip Harris, the laboratory equipment maker and pharmaceutical supplier,
announced a jump in pre-tax profits from Pounds 378,000 to Pounds 947,000
for the six months to the end of September.
There was a turnround in the education and scientific division from losses
of Pounds 148,000 to profits of Pounds 344,000 with improved sales in all
the division's areas.
Group turnover rose by 13 per cent to Pounds 50.2m (Pounds 44.3m). Earnings
per share came through at 5.77p against 2.42p and the interim dividend is
maintained at 2.2p.
Mr Bob Jordan chairman, said the general improvement in all areas of
activity pointed to an improved outcome for the full year.
