<HEADLINE>
FT  29 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Hadleigh Pounds 324,000 in the red
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pre-tax losses of Pounds 324,000 were announced by Hadleigh Industries
Group, the USM-quoted storage tank and trailer manufacturer, for the half
year to September 30. Last time there were profits of Pounds 332,000.
The result included a loss of Pounds 490,000 on the disposal of Lynton
Commercial Units in September and an operating loss from that company of
Pounds 325,000.
Turnover improved to Pounds 15.7m (Pounds 14.7m), with Pounds 2m (Pounds
2.66m) from discontinued operations.
Losses per share emerged at 3p (3.1p earnings). The interim dividend is
doubled to 1p.
</TEXT>
