FT  29 NOV 94 / UK Company News: Daniel Thwaites ahead at Pounds 3.84m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Daniel Thwaites, the brewer, wine merchant and public house and hotels
operator, lifted pre-tax profits from Pounds 3.17m to Pounds 3.84m in the
half year to September 30.
Last time there was an exceptional Pounds 565,000 loss on the sale of
properties and related plant and the result this time was also helped by
reduced interest charges of Pounds 1.92m (Pounds 2.26m).
Turnover improved to Pounds 40.2m (Pounds 38m). Earnings per share emerged
at 12.9p (9.9p) and the interim dividend is raised to 1.3p (1.2p).
The company's shares trade under Rule 535 (2).
