FT  29 NOV 94 / Electrotech plans 200 Welsh jobs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROLAND ADBURGHAM, Wales and West Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Electrotech, a UK manufacturer of machinery for making microchips, is to
transfer production from its main plant near Bristol to Newport in south
Wales.
The move is part of a Pounds 2.1m expansion intended to create an additional
200 jobs over the next three years.
The privately-owned company, which has annual sales of more than Pounds 20m,
will be moving into a 102,000 sq ft air-conditioned factory which was
formerly owned by Inmos, the UK-based semiconductor subsidiary of
SGS-Thomson.
Electrotech said it was unable to expand at its existing plant at Thornbury
and there had been no suitable alternative premises locally. All 240
full-time employees at Thornbury would be offered a transfer to Newport.
The move to the Newport factory, which has been empty for several years, has
been co-ordinated by the Welsh Development Agency.
Electrotech is acquiring the lease from Newport Wafer-Fab, which was set up
two years ago to take over manufacture at a second Inmos factory nearby.
Electrotech expects the plant to be fully operational by the middle of next
year.
